{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JzdpSRi3iH3VSYFsKBDGZZ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 14.1: WorkflowGraph Component\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want to see a schematic workflow graph in the TUI,\n11\tso that I can see all tasks, their order, and loop blocks at a glance while a workflow is running.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a running workflow with sequential flow steps `[\"create-story\", \"implement\", \"verify\"]`\n16\t   **When** the TUI renders\n17\t   **Then** the `WorkflowGraph` component displays each task as a node with its name, connected by `→` arrows in a single-line flow\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** a workflow with a loop block `{ loop: [\"implement\", \"verify\"] }`\n21\t   **When** the TUI renders\n22\t   **Then** the loop block is rendered as `loop(N)[ implement → verify ]` where N is the current iteration count (starting at 0 before any iteration, incrementing each iteration)\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** the `WorkflowGraph` component\n26\t   **When** it receives `flow`, `currentTask`, and `taskStates` as props\n27\t   **Then** each task node renders with a status indicator: pending tasks show dim text, the active task shows cyan text with a `◆` marker, completed tasks show green `✓`, and failed tasks show red `✗`\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** a workflow is running"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01UsAm2qXT84D1u4sW8gSAmJ","session_id":"a29ee53b-c2b0-4802-9455-7215112648b1","uuid":"d469f28b-ad0b-46c6-a71c-78bbef94ad8e","timestamp":"2026-04-03T11:57:26.196Z"}
