{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01J7ewFocT9UnpD6fn3ngJ7U","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015Nu6286JHMhKsdMBgpdkRq","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/14-3-activity-display-driver-integration.md","old_string":"- [ ] Task 1 (AC: #5, #6): Extend type interfaces for driver tracking\n  - [ ] In `src/lib/ink-components.tsx`, add `activeDriverName: string | null` to `RendererState`\n  - [ ] In `src/lib/ink-components.tsx`, add `driver?: string` to `CompletedToolEntry`\n  - [ ] In `src/lib/ink-components.tsx`, add `driverCosts: Record<string, number>` to `RendererState`\n  - [ ] Update initial state in `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` with `activeDriverName: null` and `driverCosts: {}`\n\n- [ ] Task 2 (AC: #3): Extend `RendererHandle.update()` with driver name parameter\n  - [ ] In `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx`, change `update(event: StreamEvent)` to `update(event: StreamEvent, driverName?: string)`\n  - [ ] Update `noopHandle` to accept the new parameter\n  - [ ] Update `RendererHandle` interface type to match\n\n- [ ] Task 3 (AC: #1, #2, #4, #9): Wire driver name into renderer state transitions\n  - [ ] In the `update()` function, on `tool-start`: set `state.activeDriverName = driverName ?? null`\n  - [ ] On `tool-start` when promoting the previous active tool to completed: include `driver: state.activeDriverName ?? undefined` in the `CompletedToolEntry`\n  - [ ] On `tool-complete`: include `driver: state.activeDriverName ?? undefined` in the `CompletedToolEntry`, then clear `state.activeDriverName` to null\n  - [ ] On `result` event with `cost_usd`: if `driverName` is provided, accumulate `state.driverCosts[driverName] += cost_usd`\n\n- [ ] Task 4 (AC: #1): Update `ActiveTool` component to show driver name\n  - [ ] In `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx`, extend `ActiveTool` props to accept `driverName?: string`\n  - [ ] Render driver name in dimmed text after the tool name (e.g., `⚡ [Bash] ` becomes `⚡ [Bash] (claude-code) `)\n  - [ ] When `driverName` is null/undefined, render as before (backward compatible)\n\n- [ ] Task 5 (AC: #2): Update `CompletedTool` component to show driver name\n  - [ ] In `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx`, extend `CompletedTool` to read `entry.driver`\n  - [ ] Render driver name in dimmed text after the args summary (e.g., `✓ [Edit] src/foo.ts (codex)`)\n  - [ ] When `entry.driver` is undefined, render as before (backward compatible)\n\n- [ ] Task 6 (AC: #8): Add driver cost summary rendering\n  - [ ] In `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx`, create a `DriverCostSummary` component that accepts `driverCosts: Record<string, number>`\n  - [ ] Renders nothing when `driverCosts` is empty\n  - [ ] Renders a single line `Cost: claude-code $X.XX, codex $Y.YY` (dimmed) when entries exist, sorted alphabetically by driver name\n  - [ ] Export from `ink-activity-components.tsx` and re-export from `ink-components.tsx`\n\n- [ ] Task 7 (AC: #8): Wire `DriverCostSummary` into the App layout\n  - [ ] In `src/lib/ink-app.tsx`, import `DriverCostSummary` and place it after `StoryBreakdown` (before the separator), passing `state.driverCosts`\n\n- [ ] Task 8 (AC: #1-#9): Write unit tests\n  - [ ] Add tests in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-activity-components.test.tsx` (NEW file):\n    - Test: `ActiveTool` renders driver name when provided\n    - Test: `ActiveTool` renders without driver name (backward compat)\n    - Test: `CompletedTool` renders driver name from entry\n    - Test: `CompletedTool` renders without driver name (backward compat)\n    - Test: `DriverCostSummary` renders nothing when empty\n    - Test: `DriverCostSummary` renders multi-driver costs sorted alphabetically\n    - Test: `DriverCostSummary` formats cost as `$X.XX`\n  - [ ] Add tests in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` (EXTEND existing):\n    - Test: `update(event, 'codex')` se