{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V3DBjhGe7LyizRS7BAKNpj","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 14.3: Activity Display Driver Integration\n2\t\n3\tStatus: review\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want to see which driver is active in the tool activity section and see per-story cost breakdown by driver,\n11\tso that I know which framework is executing the current tool call and how much each driver costs.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** stream events arriving from a driver during task execution\n16\t   **When** a `tool-start` event is processed by the renderer\n17\t   **Then** the `ActiveTool` component displays the active driver name (e.g., `claude-code`, `codex`, `opencode`) alongside the tool name, in dimmed text\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** stream events arriving from a driver during task execution\n21\t   **When** a `tool-complete` event is processed by the renderer\n22\t   **Then** the `CompletedTool` component displays the driver name that executed the tool, in dimmed text after the tool args\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** the `RendererHandle` interface\n26\t   **When** inspected\n27\t   **Then** `update(event)` accepts a second optional parameter `driverName?: string` that identifies which driver emitted the event\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** a multi-driver workflow where tasks use different drivers\n31\t   **When** the TUI activity section renders\n32\t   **Then** each tool call shows the correct driver name for the driver that dispatched it (not a global default)\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** the `RendererState` interface\n36\t   **When** inspected\n37\t   **Then** it includes an `activeDriverName: string | null` field to track which driver is currently active in the activity section\n38\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n39\t\n40\t6. **Given** the `CompletedToolEntry` interface\n41\t   **When** inspected\n42\t   **Then** it includes a `driver?: string` field to record which driver executed the tool\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t7. **Given** a per-story cost result event with `cost_usd` from a specific driver\n46\t   **When** the renderer accumulates cost data\n47\t   **Then** `RendererState` tracks per-driver cost accumulation in a `driverCosts: Record<string, number>` field\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t8. **Given** the `StoryBreakdown` component (or a new `DriverCostSummary` component)\n51\t   **When** `driverCosts` has entries for multiple drivers\n52\t   **Then** a cost-by-driver summary line is rendered (e.g., `Cost: claude-code $1.23, codex $0.45`) in dimmed text\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t9. **Given** a driver failure (error event) during task execution\n56\t   **When** the TUI renders\n57\t   **Then** the activity section continues to render normally — no freeze, no crash, the failed tool shows as completed with the driver name\n58\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n59\t\n60\t10. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n61\t    **When** the build completes\n62\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n63\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n64\t\n65\t11. **Given** `npm run test:unit` is executed after all changes\n66\t    **When** the tests complete\n67\t    **Then** all existing tests pass with zero regressions\n68\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n69\t\n70\t12. **Given** no new file exceeds 300 lines\n71\t    **When** line count is checked for all modified/created files\n72\t    **Then** every file stays under 300 lines (NFR5/NFR9)\n73\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n74\t\n75\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n76\t\n77\t- [x] Task 1 (AC: #5, #6): Extend type interfaces for driver tracking\n78\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-components.tsx`, add `activeDriverName: string | null` to `RendererState`\n79\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-components.tsx`, add `driver?: string` to `CompletedToolEntry`\n80\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-components.tsx`, add `driverCosts: Record<string, number>` to `RendererState`\n81\t  - [x] Update initial state in `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` with `activeDriverName: null` and `driverCosts: {}`\n82\t\n83\t- [x] Task 2 (AC: #3): Extend `RendererHandle.update()` with driver name parameter\n84\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx`, change `update(event: StreamEvent)` to `update(event: StreamEvent, driverName?: string)`\n85\t  - [x] Update `noopHandle` to accept the new parameter\n86\t  - [x] Update `RendererHandle` interface type to match\n87\t\n88\t- [x] Task 3 (AC: #1, #2, #4, #9): Wire driver name into renderer state transitions\n89\t  - [x] In the `update()` function, on `tool-start`: set `state.activeDriverName = driverName ?? null`\n90\t  - [x] On `tool-start` when promoting the previous active tool to completed: include `driver: state.activeDriverName ?? undefined` in the `CompletedToolEntry`\n91\t  - [x] On `tool-complete`: include `driver: state.activeDriverName ?? undefined` in the `CompletedToolEntry`, then clear `state.activeDriverName` to null\n92\t  - [x] On `result` event with `cost_usd`: if `driverName` is provided, accumulate `state.driverCosts[driverName] += cost_usd`\n93\t\n94\t- [x] Task 4 (AC: #1): Update `ActiveTool` component to show driver name\n95\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx`, extend `ActiveTool` props to accept `driverName?: string`\n96\t  - [x] Render driver name in dimmed text after the tool name (e.g., `⚡ [Bash] ` becomes `⚡ [Bash] (claude-code) `)\n97\t  - [x] When `driverName` is null/undefined, render as before (backward compatible)\n98\t\n99\t- [x] Task 5 (AC: #2): Update `CompletedTool` component to show driver name\n100\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx`, extend `CompletedTool` to read `entry.driver`\n101\t  - [x] Render driver name in dimmed text after the args summary (e.g., `✓ [Edit] src/foo.ts (codex)`)\n102\t  - [x] When `entry.driver` is undefined, render as before (backward compatible)\n103\t\n104\t- [x] Task 6 (AC: #8): Add driver cost summary rendering\n105\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx`, create a `DriverCostSummary` component that accepts `driverCosts: Record<string, number>`\n106\t  - [x] Renders nothing when `driverCosts` is empty\n107\t  - [x] Renders a single line `Cost: claude-code $X.XX, codex $Y.YY` (dimmed) when entries exist, sorted alphabetically by driver name\n108\t  - [x] Export from `ink-activity-components.tsx` and re-export from `ink-components.tsx`\n109\t\n110\t- [x] Task 7 (AC: #8): Wire `DriverCostSummary` into the App layout\n111\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-app.tsx`, import `DriverCostSummary` and place it after `StoryBreakdown` (before the separator), passing `state.driverCosts`\n112\t\n113\t- [x] Task 8 (AC: #1-#9): Write unit tests\n114\t  - [x] Add tests in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-activity-components.test.tsx` (NEW file):\n115\t    - Test: `ActiveTool` renders driver name when provided\n116\t    - Test: `ActiveTool` renders without driver name (backward compat)\n117\t    - Test: `CompletedTool` renders driver name from entry\n118\t    - Test: `CompletedTool` renders without driver name (backward compat)\n119\t    - Test: `DriverCostSummary` renders nothing when empty\n120\t    - Test: `DriverCostSummary` renders multi-driver costs sorted alphabetically\n121\t    - Test: `DriverCostSummary` formats cost as `$X.XX`\n122\t  - [x] Add tests in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` (EXTEND existing):\n123\t    - Test: `update(event, 'codex')` sets `activeDriverName` to `'codex'` on `tool-start`\n124\t    - Test: `tool-complete` records driver in `CompletedToolEntry`\n125\t    - Test: `result` event with `cost_usd` and `driverName` accumulates in `driverCosts`\n126\t    - Test: `update(event)` without driver name leaves `activeDriverName` null (backward compat)\n127\t    - Test: Driver failure event still renders normally (no crash)\n128\t\n129\t- [x] Task 9 (AC: #10): Run `npm run build` — zero TypeScript errors\n130\t- [x] Task 10 (AC: #11): Run `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, zero regressions\n131\t- [x] Task 11 (AC: #12): Verify all modified files are under 300 lines\n132\t\n133\t## Dev Notes\n134\t\n135\t### Architecture Compliance\n136\t\n137\tThis story implements Epic 5, Story 5.3 (mapped to sprint Epic 14, Story 14-3) \"Activity Display Driver Integration\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers:\n138\t- **FR31:** System can display stream events from any driver in the activity section (tool calls, thoughts, retries) — already works since all drivers emit `StreamEvent`; this story adds driver attribution.\n139\t- **FR32:** System can display the active driver name alongside tool activity — the core deliverable.\n140\t- **FR33:** System can display per-story cost breakdown by driver — `DriverCostSummary` component.\n141\t- **NFR17:** TUI must remain responsive during driver failures — AC #9 tests resilience.\n142\t\n143\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n144\t- **Decision 5 (TUI Workflow Graph Component):** Extends the activity display area under the workflow graph.\n145\t- Architecture maps FR31-FR33 to `ink-renderer.tsx` and `ink-activity-components.tsx`.\n146\t\n147\t### What Already Exists (from Stories 14-1 and 14-2)\n148\t\n149\t- `ActiveTool` component in `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` — renders `⚡ [ToolName] <spinner>`. Currently NO driver name.\n150\t- `CompletedTool` / `CompletedTools` in `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` — renders `✓ [ToolName] args`. Currently NO driver name.\n151\t- `CompletedToolEntry` in `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — `{ name: string; args: string }`. No `driver` field.\n152\t- `RendererState` in `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — has `activeTool`, `completedTools`, etc. No `activeDriverName`, no `driverCosts`.\n153\t- `update(event: StreamEvent)` in `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — handles `tool-start`, `tool-input`, `tool-complete`, `text`, `retry`, `result`. No driver tracking.\n154\t- `ResultEvent` in `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts` — already has `cost_usd?: number | null` field from Epic 13.\n155\t- `TaskNodeMeta` in `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — has `driver?: string`, `costUsd`, `elapsedMs` (from story 14-2). This is per-task-node (graph), not per-tool-call (activity).\n156\t- `noopHandle` in `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — must be updated with new `update` signature.\n157\t- Tests in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` — 881 lines. Must extend carefully (300-line budget).\n158\t\n159\t### Data Flow\n160\t\n161\tThe `update()` method is called from `createLineProcessor()` in `src/lib/run-helpers.ts`, which is called from the workflow engine's dispatch loop. Currently the `onEvent` callback only passes the event. To wire `driverName`, the calling code in `workflow-engine.ts` would need modification — **but this story only builds the TUI-layer API**. The `driverName` parameter is optional so it's backward compatible. Actual engine wiring is NOT part of this story.\n162\t\n163\tFor testing purposes, the `update()` method accepts `driverName` as a second parameter. In production, this will be wired when the engine passes driver context to the renderer callback.\n164\t\n165\t### Line Budget Analysis\n166\t\n167\t| File | Current Lines | Estimated Change | Target |\n168\t|------|--------------|------------------|--------|\n169\t| `ink-activity-components.tsx` | 100 | +50 (driver props, DriverCostSummary) | ~150 |\n170\t| `ink-components.tsx` | 213 | +5 (3 fields) | ~218 |\n171\t| `ink-renderer.tsx` | 257 | +15 (driver state, accumulation) | ~272 |\n172\t| `ink-app.tsx` | 33 | +3 (DriverCostSummary import + use) | ~36 |\n173\t| `ink-activity-components.test.tsx` | 0 (NEW) | ~180 | ~180 |\n174\t| `ink-renderer.test.tsx` | 881 | +30 (new tests) | ~911 (test files excluded from 300-line limit) |\n175\t\n176\tAll source files stay well under 300 lines. Test files are excluded from NFR5 per project convention.\n177\t\n178\t### What NOT to Do\n179\t\n180\t- Do NOT modify `workflow-engine.ts` — engine-to-renderer wiring is a future integration concern. This story makes `update()` accept an optional driver name.\n181\t- Do NOT modify `stream-parser.ts` — the `StreamEvent` types are stable.\n182\t- Do NOT modify `workflow-parser.ts` or `workflow-state.ts`.\n183\t- Do NOT modify `ink-workflow.tsx` — the workflow graph component already handles driver labels via `taskMeta` (story 14-2). This story is about the activity section below the graph.\n184\t- Do NOT add new npm dependencies. Use existing Ink primitives (`Text`, `Box`).\n185\t- Do NOT break backward compatibility — all new parameters are optional, all new fields have defaults.\n186\t\n187\t### Testing Guidance\n188\t\n189\t- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n190\t- Imports: `import { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest'`\n191\t- For activity component tests: use `ink-testing-library` `render()` + `lastFrame()` string assertions, same pattern as `ink-workflow.test.tsx`.\n192\t- For renderer tests: extend existing `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx`. The existing `makeState` helper already has `taskMeta: {}` from story 14-2 — add `activeDriverName: null` and `driverCosts: {}` to it.\n193\t- For `DriverCostSummary`: test empty state → null output, single driver, multi-driver sorted, formatting.\n194\t\n195\t### Previous Story Intelligence (14-2)\n196\t\n197\t- Story 14-2 added `TaskNodeMeta` for driver labels in the workflow graph (per-node metadata).\n198\t- This story adds driver tracking for the activity display (per-tool-call metadata). They are complementary.\n199\t- Pattern from 14-2: extend interfaces first, then components, then tests. Keep backward compatibility.\n200\t- The `ink-renderer.test.tsx` file is already large (881 lines). Add tests sparingly — focus on the new behavior, don't duplicate existing coverage.\n201\t- Activity components have NO tests yet — `src/lib/__tests__/ink-activity-components.test.tsx` does not exist. Create it.\n202\t\n203\t### Git Intelligence\n204\t\n205\tLast commit: `fcadbf7 feat: story 14-2-task-status-driver-labels — Task Status & Driver Labels`\n206\t\n207\t### References\n208\t\n209\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 5.3: Activity Display Driver Integration]\n210\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — FR31-FR33 mapped to ink-renderer.tsx, ink-activity-components.tsx]\n211\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md — FR31, FR32, FR33, NFR17]\n212\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx — ActiveTool, CompletedTool, CompletedTools components]\n213\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx — CompletedToolEntry, RendererState interfaces]\n214\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx — RendererHandle, update(), startRenderer()]\n215\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts — ResultEvent.cost_usd field]\n216\t\n217\t## Files to Change\n218\t\n219\t- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — Add `driver?: string` to `CompletedToolEntry`, add `activeDriverName: string | null` and `driverCosts: Record<string, number>` to `RendererState`.\n220\t- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — Extend `update()` with `driverName` param, update `RendererHandle` type, update `noopHandle`, wire driver state in event handlers.\n221\t- `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` — Extend `ActiveTool` and `CompletedTool` with driver name display, add `DriverCostSummary` component.\n222\t- `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` — Import and render `DriverCostSummary` from state.\n223\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-activity-components.test.tsx` — NEW: unit tests for activity components with driver names and cost summary.\n224\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` — EXTEND: add tests for driver name in `update()`, driver cost accumulation, `activeDriverName` state.\n225\t\n226\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n227\t## Verification Requirements\n228\t\n229\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/14-3-activity-display-driver-integration.proof.md`)\n230\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n231\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n232\t\n233\t## Documentation Requirements\n234\t\n235\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n236\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/14-3-activity-display-driver-integration.md`\n237\t\n238\t## Testing Requirements\n239\t\n240\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n241\t- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n242\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n243\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n244\t\n245\t## Dev Agent Record\n246\t\n247\t### Agent Model Used\n248\t\n249\tclaude-opus-4-6\n250\t\n251\t### Debug Log References\n252\t\n253\tN/A\n254\t\n255\t### Completion Notes List\n256\t\n257\t- All 11 tasks completed. 15 new tests added (10 activity component, 5 renderer driver integration).\n258\t- Build passes with zero TypeScript errors. Full test suite: 4591 tests, 170 files, zero regressions.\n259\t- All source files under 300 lines (ink-components: 216, ink-renderer: 270, ink-activity-components: 110, ink-app: 34).\n260\t- Added defensive null check to DriverCostSummary for runtime safety.\n261\t\n262\t### Change Log\n263\t\n264\t- 2026-04-03: Story created with 12 ACs (3 from epic FR31-FR33, 9 derived from architecture, testing, and code analysis). Full implementation guidance with line budgets, data flow analysis, and anti-patterns. Status set to ready-for-dev.\n265\t- 2026-04-03: Implementation complete. All tasks done, all tests passing. Status set to review.\n266\t\n267\t### File List\n268\t\n269\t- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — Added `driver?` to CompletedToolEntry, `activeDriverName` and `driverCosts` to RendererState, re-exported DriverCostSummary\n270\t- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — Extended `update()` with `driverName` param, updated noopHandle, wired driver state in event handlers, added per-driver cost accumulation\n271\t- `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` — Extended ActiveTool/CompletedTool with driver display, added DriverCostSummary component\n272\t- `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` — Imported DriverCostSummary, wired into layout, passed driverName to ActiveTool\n273\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-activity-components.test.tsx` — NEW: 10 tests for activity components with driver names and cost summary\n274\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` — Extended: 5 new tests for driver name in update(), driver cost accumulation, backward compat, failure resilience\n275\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0117vDhwD8YtdmVSBCbGt4wb","session_id":"a29ee53b-c2b0-4802-9455-7215112648b1","uuid":"317d250d-e9ea-4bed-8179-07f6ad9a3d92","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:09:24.526Z"}
