{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0117vDhwD8YtdmVSBCbGt4wb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Test files are excluded from the 300-line NFR per project convention. Source files were not modified, all remain under 300 lines.\n\n---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 14-3-activity-display-driver-integration\n**Status:** review → verifying\n**Build:** Clean (zero TypeScript errors)\n**Tests:** 4598 passing (7 net new), 170 test files\n**Coverage:** 96.86% overall, all 171 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n### Fixes Applied\n\n1. **H1 (HIGH):** Rewrote renderer driver tests — added 6 new `App` component rendering tests with real `expect()` assertions that verify driver names appear in active tools, completed tools, and cost summary output. The original 5 \"no crash\" tests were retained as controller integration smoke tests but are no longer the only coverage.\n\n2. **H2/M3 (HIGH/MEDIUM):** Added `App`-level integration tests that verify `DriverCostSummary` renders correctly in the full layout — both multi-driver and empty states.\n\n3. **M2 (MEDIUM):** Added test proving driver name renders after truncated long args (80-char args with `opencode` driver suffix).\n\n### Files Modified\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` — Replaced 5 assertion-free smoke tests with 6 assertion-based App rendering tests + 5 controller integration tests (11 total, was 5)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/ink-activity-components.test.tsx` — Added 1 test for long args + driver suffix\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/14-3-activity-display-driver-integration.md` — Status → verifying, review entry in Change Log\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- **HIGH:** Renderer driver tests (5 tests) had zero `expect()` assertions — only verified no exceptions. Fixed.\n- **HIGH:** No test verified `DriverCostSummary` renders in the `App` layout. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM:** No test for driver name surviving args truncation (60-char limit + driver suffix). Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `DriverCostSummary` has a redundant two-stage null guard (`!driverCosts` then `entries.length === 0`). Functional but slightly confusing. Low priority.\n- Story File List doesn't mention App-level testing gap. Documentation-only issue.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Controller integration tests (`startRenderer` + `update()`) still have no state assertions — they verify \"no throw\" but can't inspect internal `RendererState`. This is an architectural limitation (state is closure-scoped). The new `App` rendering tests compensate by testing the same behavior at the component layer.\n- No test for `DriverCostSummary` rendering with very long driver names or special characters.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The `update()` method's `driverName` parameter is wired at the TUI layer but NOT connected to the workflow engine dispatch loop. The engine → renderer callback in `run-helpers.ts` does not pass `driverName`. This is documented as out-of-scope for this story, but means the feature is inert in production until a future integration story wires it.\n- `CompletedTool` uses `wrap=\"truncate-end\"` which may silently clip the driver suffix in narrow terminals (<80 columns). No mitigation possible without changing the display design.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:** None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 10, Edit: 3, Grep: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit` (~30 lines), `git diff/status` (~25 lines), `npx codeharness coverage` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 11 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: None. Each read targeted a distinct file or offset."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a6c98b1d5c5259515 (use SendMessage with to: 'a6c98