{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SxBR1wBuPZVNA1erhRanhp","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 9)\n2\t\n3\t### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — create-story (2026-04-03T09:20)\n4\t\n5\t- **Ambiguity: OpenCode CLI output format.** Architecture doc acknowledges must be \"reverse-engineered from real CLI output.\" Fixtures will be plausible guesses.\n6\t- **Ambiguity: OpenCode auth check command.** Used `opencode auth status` as guess. Low risk — health check gracefully handles command failure.\n7\t- **No project-context.md found** — workflow references it but none exists. No impact.\n8\t- **Risk: classifyError duplication.** Both CodexDriver and OpenCodeDriver have identical implementations. Intentional per architecture.\n9\t\n10\tToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 7, Grep: 4, Glob: 2, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 10 unique files. No redundancy.\n11\t\n12\t### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — dev-story (2026-04-03T09:25)\n13\t\n14\tNo issues reported. Build passes, 4478 tests pass across 166 test files, zero regressions.\n15\t\n16\tToken Report: 20 tool calls (Bash: 4, Read: 11, Edit: 3, Write: 6, Glob: 2, Skill: 1). 11 unique files, 12 total reads. No redundancy.\n17\t\n18\t### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — code-review (2026-04-03T09:30)\n19\t\n20\t- **LOW: Dead fixture files.** test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/*.txt exist but tests use inline data. Dead artifacts.\n21\t- **LOW: classifyError/parseLine duplication.** ~80 identical lines between codex.ts and opencode.ts. Intentional per architecture.\n22\t- **LOW: console.debug for unparseable lines.** No structured logger. Shared pattern across drivers.\n23\t- No HIGH or MEDIUM issues. 96.78% coverage. All 169 files above 80% floor.\n24\t\n25\tToken Report: 12 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 7, Edit: 1, Grep: 1, Glob: 3, Skill: 1). 8 unique files. No redundancy.\n26\t\n27\t### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — verify (2026-04-03T09:35)\n28\t\n29\t- **Stale AGENTS.md precondition:** `codeharness verify` fails due to stale AGENTS.md files for src/lib/agents/drivers module. Pre-existing documentation debt, not story-related.\n30\t- **Test count discrepancy:** Story changelog claims 64 tests, actual count is 69. Minor — 69 is current state.\n31\t- **Branch coverage 96.03%:** 4 uncovered branches at lines 149, 198, 306-307 (edge cases in parseLine result handling and error catch block).\n32\t- ALL_PASS: 11/11 ACs verified with evidence.\n33\t\n34\tToken Report: 11 tool calls (Bash: 7, Read: 3, Write: 1). 3 unique files. No redundancy.\n35\t\n36\t### 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start — create-story (2026-04-03T09:39)\n37\t\n38\t- **Multiple epics files with different 12-3 definitions.** Correct source is epics-multi-framework.md based on sprint-status context.\n39\t- **Risk: 5-second timeout NFR6** requires careful mock design with fake timers to avoid real waits in tests.\n40\t- All 9 ACs tagged test-provable. Small, well-scoped story (~100-150 lines prod, ~150-200 lines tests).\n41\t\n42\tToken Report: 21 tool calls (Bash: 2, Read: 8, Grep: 7, Write: 1, Glob: 3, Skill: 1). 10 unique files. No redundancy.\n43\t\n44\t### 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start — dev-story (2026-04-03T09:45)\n45\t\n46\t- **Workaround: optional timeoutMs parameter** added to `checkDriverHealth()` for testability (fake timers caused unhandled rejection warnings). Clean solution, not in original spec.\n47\t- **Existing test impact:** Updated `healthCheck` mock in workflow-engine.test.ts to return valid `DriverHealth` object. Updated `mockGetDriver` call count assertion (+1 for health check).\n48\t- **Code quality concern:** `setTimeout` in `checkDriverHealth` not cleared after `Promise.all` resolves — standard Promise.race behavior but could use cleanup.\n49\t- Build passes (0 errors), 4488 tests pass across 167 files, zero regressions.\n50\t\n51\tToken Report: 19 tool calls (Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 1). 6 unique files, 10 total reads. workflow-engine.test.ts read 4x, workflow-engine.ts read 3x. One redundant npm run build call.\n52\t\n53\t### 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start — code-review (2026-04-03T09:51)\n54\t\n55\t- **HIGH: Timer leak fixed.** `setTimeout` never cleared on success path in `checkDriverHealth()`. Added `clearTimeout`.\n56\t- **MEDIUM: Timeout error inaccuracy fixed.** Was reporting ALL drivers instead of only non-responding ones (AC #6 violation).\n57\t- **MEDIUM: Double mock invocation fixed.** Test called `checkDriverHealth` twice per assertion.\n58\t- **MEDIUM: Missing test added.** \"timeout error reports only drivers that did not respond\".\n59\t- **LOW (not fixed): `HealthResult` type** defined inline in function body rather than module scope. Cosmetic.\n60\t- Coverage: 96.79% overall, all 169 files above 80% floor.\n61\t\n62\tToken Report: 21 tool calls (Bash: 10, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 8 unique files. No redundancy.\n63\t\n64\t### 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start — verify (2026-04-03T09:55)\n65\t\n66\t- **Proof format mismatch:** Verifier subagent generated `### AC N:` headers but parser expects `## AC N:`. Also needed `bash`/`output` code block pairs. Manually rewrote proof document.\n67\t- **Stale AGENTS.md files:** Fixed src/lib/agents/AGENTS.md, src/lib/AGENTS.md, created src/lib/agents/drivers/AGENTS.md. Pre-existing debt from stories 12-1/12-2.\n68\t- **Pre-existing lint error:** `require-yield` at workflow-engine.test.ts:154. Not from this story.\n69\t- ALL_PASS: 9/9 ACs verified. `codeharness verify` passes.\n70\t\n71\tToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 2, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 3 unique files. npm run test:unit run twice (verbose + summary).\n72\t\n73\t### 13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization — create-story (2026-04-03T10:04)\n74\t\n75\t- **Ambiguity: contract directory parameter vs hardcoded path.** Architecture says `.codeharness/contract