{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ConxeX1LP9UTiusvy9DPHY","type":"tool_result","content":"4305\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 11)\n4306\t\n4307\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T15:30Z\n4308\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T11:36 to ~2026-04-03T15:30 (approx. 4 hours)\n4309\t**Sprint progress:** 42/47 stories done (89.4%), Epics 1-13 complete, Epic 14 at 2/3\n4310\t\n4311\t---\n4312\t\n4313\t## 1. Session Summary\n4314\t\n4315\tSession 11 completed one story through the full lifecycle (create -> dev -> code-review -> verify -> done).\n4316\t\n4317\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n4318\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n4319\t| 14-2-task-status-driver-labels | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify | **Done** | Full lifecycle. 11/11 ACs passed. |\n4320\t\n4321\t**Key deliverables:**\n4322\t- Driver name labels on active/completed task rows in WorkflowGraph\n4323\t- Cost display (`$0.04`) alongside task status\n4324\t- Elapsed time formatting (`12s`, `2m`) per task\n4325\t- Text-based braille spinner for active tasks (no `ink-spinner` dependency)\n4326\t- Column-aligned metadata display (driver, cost, elapsed)\n4327\t- 29 workflow tests running in 39ms, 100% line/statement coverage, 94.82% branch coverage\n4328\t\n4329\t**Context:** This session also ran in the broader context of Sessions 9-10 on the same day, which completed stories 12-2, 12-3, 13-1, 13-2, 13-3, and 14-1. Session 11 was the continuation, picking up 14-2 as the next story after 14-1.\n4330\t\n4331\t---\n4332\t\n4333\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n4334\t\n4335\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n4336\t\n4337\t| Severity | Issue | Impact |\n4338\t|----------|-------|--------|\n4339\t| HIGH | `formatElapsed` rounding bug — `Math.round(seconds/60)` inflated displayed minutes (90s showed \"2m\" instead of \"1m\") | User-facing display error. Fixed with `Math.floor`. |\n4340\t| MEDIUM | Column alignment bug — driver/cost rows used 5-space separators vs 3-col arrow width | Visual misalignment in TUI. Fixed. |\n4341\t| MEDIUM | Misleading comment — \"ref-based counter\" with no ref | Code clarity. Rewrote. |\n4342\t| MEDIUM | Missing test coverage — no tests for `formatElapsed(0)`, fractional minutes boundary, loop-with-meta | Gap in edge case coverage. Added 3 tests. |\n4343\t\n4344\t### LOW Issues Deferred (tech debt)\n4345\t\n4346\t- **Spinner non-determinism:** `Date.now()` for spinner frame index means tests assert \"any frame\" rather than a specific one. Not easily testable without injecting a clock.\n4347\t- **Column alignment fragile:** Manual space counting for column alignment. Should use `string-width` for proper Unicode-aware padding. Will break with long task names or non-ASCII characters.\n4348\t\n4349\t### Verification Gaps\n4350\t\n4351\t- **AC 8 (NFR2 500ms render performance):** Verified by code inspection (no artificial delays, no blocking I/O) rather than runtime timing measurement. Strong but indirect evidence — no actual timing benchmark.\n4352\t- **Branch coverage 94.82%:** 5.18% uncovered branches — likely defensive null checks and edge cases in spinner frame calculation.\n4353\t\n4354\t### Infrastructure Issues\n4355\t\n4356\t- **Pre-existing `require-yield` lint error:** Still present in unrelated file. This has been flagged in every session since Session 5. Trivial fix, never prioritized.\n4357\t- **`codeharness stats --save` still requires workaround:** The command fails without `session-logs/` directory. Cost report was generated only because the error handler falls through to print the report before exiting. This is session 5+ of this being broken.\n4358\t- **No project-context.md:** Workflow references it but none exists. Flagged in create-story but not blocking.\n4359\t- **Config.yaml path mismatch:** Workflow expected `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml`, actual is `_bmad/config.yaml`. Minor.\n4360\t\n4361\t### Workarounds Applied\n4362\t\n4363\t- Used `Date.now()` for spinner frame index instead of proper animation timer — only advances on re-render, not on interval. Acceptable for current architecture but not smooth animation.\n4364\t- Simple spacing for column alignment instead of precise column-width calculations.\n4365\t- No `ink-spinner` dependency — implemented text-based braille frames inline.\n4366\t\n4367\t---\n4368\t\n4369\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n4370\t\n4371\t### Global Cost Summary (from cost-report.md)\n4372\t\n4373\t| Metric | Value |\n4374\t|--------|-------|\n4375\t| Total API-equivalent cost (all sessions) | $250.40 |\n4376\t| Total API calls (all sessions) | 1,936 |\n4377\t| Average cost per story | $3.41 |\n4378\t| Total stories tracked | 62 (includes all phases across all stories) |\n4379\t\n4380\t### Cost by Phase (cumulative, all sessions)\n4381\t\n4382\t| Phase | Calls | Cost | % |\n4383\t|-------|-------|------|---|\n4384\t| verify | 947 | $113.94 | 45.5% |\n4385\t| orchestrator | 214 | $44.84 | 17.9% |\n4386\t| create-story | 235 | $26.87 | 10.7% |\n4387\t| dev-story | 234 | $26.16 | 10.4% |\n4388\t| code-review | 184 | $21.80 | 8.7% |\n4389\t| retro | 122 | $16.78 | 6.7% |\n4390\t\n4391\t**Verification remains the dominant cost at 45.5%.** This is consistent across all 11 sessions. The verify phase runs the most API calls (947 of 1,936 = 49%) and consumes the most tokens because it reads test output, coverage reports, and generates proof documents.\n4392\t\n4393\t### Cost by Token Type\n4394\t\n4395\t| Type | Tokens | Cost | % |\n4396\t|------|--------|------|---|\n4397\t| Cache reads | 103M | $154.55 | 62% |\n4398\t| Cache writes | 2.9M | $54.91 | 22% |\n4399\t| Output | 545K | $40.84 | 16% |\n4400\t| Input | 6K | $0.09 | 0% |\n4401\t\n4402\tCache reads dominate at 62% — this is structural. Long-running sessions accumulate large context windows that get cached. Output tokens (16%) are the actual \"work\" — code generation, proof documents, test code.\n4403\t\n4404\t### Subagent Token Report (Session 11 only)\n4405\t\n4406\tAggregated from `.session-issues.md` token reports for story 14-2:\n4407\t\n4408\t| Subagent Phase | Tool Calls | Top Tools | Notable |\n4409\t|---------------|------------|-----------|---------|\n4410\t| create-story | 20 | Read: 8, Grep: 5, Glob: 5 | 10 unique files, 11 total reads |\n4411\t| dev-story | 22 | Edit: 10, Read: 9, Bash: 5 | 9 unique files; ink-workflow.tsx read 2x |\n4412\t| code-review | 19 | Bash: 9, Read: 8, Edit: 6 | 9 unique files; no redundancy |\n4413\t| verify | 14 | Bash: 9, Read: 1, Grep: 5 | 1 unique file; vitest run 2x (could combine) |\n4414\t| **Session Total** | **75** | Read: 26, Bash: 23, Edit: 16, Grep: 15 | |\n4415\t\n4416\t### Subagent-Level Observations\n4417\t\n4418\t- **Create-story is Read/Grep heavy** (13 of 20 calls): reads architecture docs, PRD, epics, existing components. This is necessary context-gathering.\n4419\t- **Dev-story is Edit-heavy** (10 of 22 calls): expected for implementation work.\n4420\t- **Code-review is Bash-heavy** (9 of 19 calls): runs tests after each fix. The fix-verify loop is inherent to the review process.\n4421\t- **Verify phase ran vitest twice** (coverage run + verbose names). Could be combined into a single `vitest --coverage --reporter=verbose` call. Minor waste.\n4422\t- **ink-workflow.tsx read twice in dev-story**: once for initial understanding, once for Edit context. Acceptable.\n4423\t- **No cross-phase file redundancy**: each phase reads its own needed context without re-reading files already processed by prior phases.\n4424\t\n4425\t### Estimated Session 11 Cost\n4426\t\n4427\tAt 75 subagent tool calls plus orchestrator overhead, estimated **$4-6** for this session (consistent with the $3.41/story average, accounting for orchestrator overhead and the retro phase).\n4428\t\n4429\t### Wasted Spend\n4430\t\n4431\t- **Vitest double-run in verify:** ~$0.10-0.20 (minor).\n4432\t- **No significant wasted spend this session.** Single story, clean lifecycle, no retries, no stuck phases.\n4433\t\n4434\t### Cross-Session Cost Trend\n4435\t\n4436\t| Session | Stories | Est. Cost | Cost/Story |\n4437\t|---------|---------|-----------|------------|\n4438\t| Sessions 1-8 (prior days) | ~35 | ~$200 | ~$5.71 |\n4439\t| Session 9 (12-2, 12-3) | 2 | ~$12 | ~$6.00 |\n4440\t| Session 10 (13-1 thru 14-1) | 6 | ~$30 | ~$5.00 |\n4441\t| Session 11 (14-2) | 1 | ~$5 | ~$5.00 |\n4442\t| **Cumulative** | **~44** | **$250.40** | **$5.69** |\n4443\t\n4444\tNote: The cost report averages $3.41/story across 62 \"stories\" but this counts each phase invocation separately. The effective cost per completed story (lifecycle) is closer to $5-6.\n4445\t\n4446\t---\n4447\t\n4448\t## 4. What Went Well\n4449\t\n4450\t1. **Clean single-story lifecycle.** 14-2 went from backlog to verified in one session with no retries, no stuck phases, and no escalations. All 11 ACs passed.\n4451\t2. **Code review caught a real user-facing bug.** The `Math.round` vs `Math.floor` bug in `formatElapsed` would have shown incorrect elapsed times to users. HIGH severity, caught before merge.\n4452\t3. **Good test coverage.** 100% line/statement, 94.82% branch, 29 tests in 39ms. The TUI component testing pattern with `ink-testing-library` is working well.\n4453\t4. **No spinner dependency bloat.** Instead of adding `ink-spinner` as a dependency, a lightweight text-based braille spinner was implemented inline. Fewer dependencies = less maintenance.\n4454\t5. **Session issues log continues to be valuable.** Subagent self-reporting of tool calls and issues made this retrospective possible without working `codeharness stats`.\n4455\t6. **Prior session recommendation followed.** Session 10 recommended \"Continue Epic 14: stories 14-2 and 14-3.\" This session executed on that recommendation.\n4456\t\n4457\t---\n4458\t\n4459\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n4460\t\n4461\t1. **Only 1 story completed in ~4 hours.** While the story was clean, throughput is lower than Sessions 9-10 which completed 2 and 6 stories respectively. Likely due to session context overhead or longer orchestrator pauses between phases.\n4462\t2. **`codeharness stats --save` still broken** (session 5+ of this being reported). The cost report was only generated because the error falls through. This tooling gap makes cost analysis unreliable.\n4463\t3. **Pre-existing lint error still unfixed** (`require-yield`). 6+ sessions of noise in every lint check. Trivial fix that keeps getting deprioritized.\n4464\t4. **Spinner non-determinism introduced.** `Date.now()` based frame selection is inherently untestable for exact frame assertions. This is minor but adds to the \"test approximation\" debt.\n4465\t5. **Column alignment uses manual spacing.** Fragile approach that will break with different terminal widths or long task names. Should use `string-width` or Ink's `<Box>` layout.\n4466\t\n4467\t---\n4468\t\n4469\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n4470\t\n4471\t### Patterns to Repeat\n4472\t\n4473\t1. **Lightweight alternatives to npm dependencies.** The braille spinner is 4 characters in an array vs a full `ink-spinner` package. For simple needs, inline is better.\n4474\t2. **Code review finding math bugs.** `Math.round` vs `Math.floor` for time formatting is a classic bug class. Code review caught it; tests didn't (because the test values were within rounding range). Reviews complement tests.\n4475\t3. **Single-story focused sessions.** No cross-story pollution, clean context, clean lifecycle. The overhead per story is slightly higher but the quality is consistently good.\n4476\t\n4477\t### Patterns to Avoid\n4478\t\n4479\t1. **Running vitest twice in verify phase.** Once with coverage, once with verbose names. Combine into one call.\n4480\t2. **Deferring trivial fixes indefinitely.** The `require-yield` lint fix and `codeharness stats` fix have been carried forward for 5-6 sessions. At some point the accumulated noise costs more than the fix.\n4481\t3. **Manual column alignment in TUI components.** Use layout primitives (`<Box>`, `<Spacer>`) or `string-width` for proper alignment. Manual spacing is fragile and hard to maintain.\n4482\t\n4483\t---\n4484\t\n4485\t## 7. Action Items\n4486\t\n4487\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n4488\t|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n4489\t| 64 | Fix proof format template — embed exact format spec in verify skill prompt | HIGH | Tooling | Carry-forward (no regression this session) |\n4490\t| 65 | Auto-generate AGENTS.md during dev-story phase | HIGH | Process | Carry-forward |\n4491\t| 66 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work without session-logs directory | MEDIUM | Tooling | Carry-forward (5+ sessions) |\n4492\t| 67 | Fix pre-existing `require-yield` lint error in workflow-engine.test.ts | LOW | Cleanup | Carry-forward (6+ sessions) |\n4493\t| 68 | Extract shared driver utilities (classifyError, parseLine) to common module | MEDIUM | Cleanup | Carry-forward |\n4494\t| 69 | Split workflow-engine.test.ts into smaller focused test files | MEDIUM | Cleanup | Carry-forward |\n4495\t| 73 | Remove `currentTask` dead code prop from WorkflowGraph or wire it | LOW | Cleanup | Carry-forward |\n4496\t| 76 | Replace manual column spacing in ink-workflow.tsx with `string-width` or Ink layout | MEDIUM | Cleanup | New |\n4497\t| 77 | Combine vitest coverage + verbose into single command in verify phase | LOW | Process | New |\n4498\t| 78 | Complete story 14-3-activity-display-driver-integration to close Epic 14 | HIGH | Next session | New |\n4499\t| 79 | Inject clock/timer for spinner frame index to enable deterministic tests | LOW | Cleanup | New |\n4500\t\n4501\t### Priority Recommendations for Next Session\n4502\t\n4503\t1. **Story 14-3** — complete Epic 14 (Dashboard & Visualization). Only 1 story remaining.\n4504\t2. **Fix `require-yield` lint (#67)** — 6 sessions of noise. Just do it."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01371Pi8Xv61ym8B24cArBdj","session_id":"a29ee53b-c2b0-4802-9455-7215112648b1","uuid":"6c06f86b-f140-4773-b2ed-c4444e836aaf","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:19:52.095Z"}
