{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Xj7TmU2jSNnJs5t15ZHneK","type":"tool_result","content":"3702\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 13, Current Sprint Final)\n3703\t\n3704\t**Generated:** 2026-04-03T14:30:00Z\n3705\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T09:20 to ~2026-04-03T14:22 (approx. 5 hours)\n3706\t**Sprint progress:** 35/46 stories done (76%), Epics 1-12 complete, Epic 13 at 2/3\n3707\t\n3708\t---\n3709\t\n3710\t## 1. Session Summary\n3711\t\n3712\tThis session ran stories from Epics 12 and 13 — the multi-framework driver layer and output contract system.\n3713\t\n3714\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | ACs | Attempts | Notes |\n3715\t|-------|-----------|---------|-----|----------|-------|\n3716\t| 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation | create-story, dev, code-review, verify | **Done** | 11/11 | 1 | Full lifecycle. 69 tests. 96.78% coverage. |\n3717\t| 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start | create-story, dev, code-review, verify | **Done** | 9/9 | 2 | Timer leak caught and fixed in code review. |\n3718\t| 13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization | create-story, dev, code-review, verify | **Done** | 10/10 | 1 | Path traversal vuln caught in review. |\n3719\t| 13-2-output-contract-prompt-injection | create-story, dev, code-review, verify | **Done** | 12/12 | 1 | Dead wiring bug caught in review (dispatchTask). |\n3720\t\n3721\t**Net output:** 4 stories completed and verified. Epic 12 closed. Epic 13 at 2/3.\n3722\t**Test suite:** 4506 tests across 170 files. 96.8% statement coverage. All files above 80% floor.\n3723\t\n3724\t---\n3725\t\n3726\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n3727\t\n3728\t### 2.1 Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed in session)\n3729\t\n3730\t| Severity | Story | Issue |\n3731\t|----------|-------|-------|\n3732\t| HIGH | 12-3 | Timer leak — `setTimeout` never cleared on success path in `checkDriverHealth()` |\n3733\t| HIGH | 13-1 | Path traversal — `taskName` with `../` could write outside `contractDir` |\n3734\t| HIGH | 13-1 | Empty input validation — empty `taskName`/`storyId` produced nonsensical filenames |\n3735\t| MEDIUM | 12-3 | Timeout error reported ALL drivers instead of only non-responding ones (AC #6 violation) |\n3736\t| MEDIUM | 12-3 | Test double mock called `checkDriverHealth` twice per assertion |\n3737\t| MEDIUM | 13-1 | JSON parse error handling missing for corrupted contract files |\n3738\t| MEDIUM | 13-1 | Platform guard missing for `chmodSync` test (Windows) |\n3739\t| MEDIUM | 13-2 | `dispatchTask()` public API missing `previousOutputContract` — dead wiring for story 13-3 |\n3740\t| MEDIUM | 13-2 | No workflow engine integration test for contract injection (AC #10) |\n3741\t| MEDIUM | 13-2 | Missing boundary test for output truncation at exactly 2001 characters |\n3742\t\n3743\t**Code review caught 3 HIGH bugs this session.** The path traversal in 13-1 and timer leak in 12-3 would have been production defects. Review continues to be the highest-value phase per dollar spent.\n3744\t\n3745\t### 2.2 Workarounds Applied (tech debt introduced)\n3746\t\n3747\t| Story | Workaround | Risk |\n3748\t|-------|-----------|------|\n3749\t| 12-2 | OpenCode CLI output format reverse-engineered from guesses; fixtures are plausible but unverified | Will break when real CLI is tested |\n3750\t| 12-2 | `opencode auth status` as health check command — guessed | Low — graceful failure on command miss |\n3751\t| 12-3 | Optional `timeoutMs` parameter added to `checkDriverHealth()` for testability (fake timers caused warnings) | Clean, but not in original spec |\n3752\t| 13-1 | `output_contract` naming overlap with existing workflow schema field acknowledged but not resolved | Confusion risk in 13-3 |\n3753\t\n3754\t### 2.3 Code Quality Concerns (deferred LOW issues)\n3755\t\n3756\t- **classifyError/parseLine duplication:** ~80 identical lines between codex.ts and opencode.ts. Intentional per architecture but growing.\n3757\t- **Dead fixture files:** `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/*.txt` exist but tests use inline data.\n3758\t- **`HealthResult` type defined inline** in function body rather than module scope.\n3759\t- **No markdown sanitization** in `formatContractAsPromptContext`.\n3760\t- **`toFixed(2)` cost formatting** shows `$0.00` for sub-cent costs.\n3761\t- **No runtime schema validation** at contract write time (by design per story spec).\n3762\t- **`console.debug` for unparseable lines** — no structured logger, shared pattern across drivers.\n3763\t\n3764\t### 2.4 Verification Gaps\n3765\t\n3766\tNo escalated ACs. All 42 ACs (11+9+10+12) passed with evidence.\n3767\t\n3768\tRecurring friction:\n3769\t- **Stale AGENTS.md blocks `codeharness verify`** — happened in 12-2, 12-3, and 13-1. Pre-existing documentation debt, not story-related, but burns verify cycles every time.\n3770\t- **Proof format mismatches:** Verify subagent generated wrong header format twice (12-3 used `### AC N:` instead of `## AC N:`; 13-2 used `**Status:** PASS` instead of `**Verdict:** PASS`). Manual rewrites needed.\n3771\t- **Test count discrepancies:** Story 12-2 changelog claimed 64 tests, actual count was 69.\n3772\t\n3773\t### 2.5 Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n3774\t\n3775\t- **`codeharness stats --save` fails** with \"No session-logs/ directory found\" — ralph logs exist but stats command looks in a different path.\n3776\t- **sprint-state.json epic sync bug persists:** Epics 10, 11, 13, 14, 15 show `storiesDone: 0` despite all stories being done in 10-12. Known from previous sessions.\n3777\t- **Pre-existing `require-yield` lint error** in `workflow-engine.test.ts:154` — not from any current story but blocks clean lint runs.\n3778\t- **Multiple epics files with conflicting 12-3 definitions** — had to identify correct source manually.\n3779\t\n3780\t---\n3781\t\n3782\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n3783\t\n3784\t### 3.1 Total Sprint Cost\n3785\t\n3786\t| Metric | Value |\n3787\t|--------|-------|\n3788\t| **Total API-equivalent cost** | **$202.85** |\n3789\t| **Total API calls** | 1,568 |\n3790\t| **Average cost per story** | $3.46 (across 49 stories tracked) |\n3791\t| **Stories completed this session** | 4 |\n3792\t| **Estimated session cost** | ~$14-18 (4 stories at ~$3.50-4.50 each) |\n3793\t\n3794\t### 3.2 Cost by Phase (full sprint)\n3795\t\n3796\t| Phase | Calls | Cost | % | Observation |\n3797\t|-------|-------|------|---|-------------|\n3798\t| **verify** | 749 | $89.96 | 44.3% | Most expensive phase by far |\n3799\t| orchestrator | 175 | $37.21 | 18.3% | Ralph loop overhead |\n3800\t| create-story | 207 | $23.29 | 11.5% | Story spec generation |\n3801\t| dev-story | 182 | $20.26 | 10.0% | Actual implementation |\n3802\t| code-review | 158 | $18.61 | 9.2% | Adversarial review |\n3803\t| retro | 97 | $13.52 | 6.7% | Retrospectives |\n3804\t\n3805\t**Verification is 44% of spend.** This is the dominant cost driver. It includes AGENTS.md staleness fixes, proof format rewrites, and re-runs of test suites.\n3806\t\n3807\t### 3.3 Cost by Token Type\n3808\t\n3809\t| Type | Cost | % | Note |\n3810\t|------|------|---|------|\n3811\t| Cache reads (83M tokens) | $124.55 | 61% | Context re-reading dominates |\n3812\t| Cache writes (2.4M tokens) | $45.29 | 22% | New context creation |\n3813\t| Output (439K tokens) | $32.92 | 16% | Generated code and text |\n3814\t| Input (5.6K tokens) | $0.08 | <1% | Negligible |\n3815\t\n3816\tThe 83M cache read tokens indicate massive context re-reading. Each subagent phase loads the full project context.\n3817\t\n3818\t### 3.4 Cost by Tool\n3819\t\n3820\t| Tool | Calls | Cost | % |\n3821\t|------|-------|------|---|\n3822\t| Bash | 485 | $53.58 | 26.4% |\n3823\t| Read | 360 | $49.05 | 24.2% |\n3824\t| Edit | 316 | $38.71 | 19.1% |\n3825\t| Agent | 195 | $28.36 | 14.0% |\n3826\t| Skill | 36 | $13.33 | 6.6% |\n3827\t\n3828\t### 3.5 Subagent-Level Token Breakdown (This Session)\n3829\t\n3830\tAggregated from session issues log Token Report sections:\n3831\t\n3832\t| Story | Phase | Tool Calls | Key Observation |\n3833\t|-------|-------|-----------|-----------------|\n3834\t| 12-2 | create-story | 16 | 10 unique files, no redundancy |\n3835\t| 12-2 | dev-story | 20 | 12 total reads vs 11 unique files — minimal |\n3836\t| 12-2 | code-review | 12 | Clean |\n3837\t| 12-2 | verify | 11 | Clean |\n3838\t| 12-3 | create-story | 21 | 7 Grep calls (searching multiple epic files) |\n3839\t| 12-3 | dev-story | 19 | workflow-engine.test.ts read 4x, workflow-engine.ts read 3x. 1 redundant `npm run build` |\n3840\t| 12-3 | code-review | 21 | 10 Bash calls (highest this session) |\n3841\t| 12-3 | verify | 14 | `npm run test:unit` run twice (verbose + summary) |\n3842\t| 13-1 | create-story | 14 | 5 Glob calls (scanning for contract patterns) |\n3843\t| 13-1 | dev-story | 17 | 1 re-read for Edit mismatch |\n3844\t| 13-1 | code-review | 22 | 10 Bash calls, 8 Read calls |\n3845\t| 13-1 | verify | 14 | Clean |\n3846\t| 13-2 | create-story | 24 | 7 Grep + 4 Glob — heaviest create-story this session |\n3847\t| 13-2 | dev-story | 13 | Leanest dev this session |\n3848\t| 13-2 | code-review | 25 | Heaviest code-review (workflow-engine.test.ts read 3x) |\n3849\t| 13-2 | verify | 14 | Clean |\n3850\t\n3851\t**Session totals:** ~277 tool calls across 16 subagent invocations.\n3852\t\n3853\t**Redundancy hotspots:**\n3854\t- `workflow-engine.test.ts` read 7+ times across phases (4x in 12-3 dev, 3x in 13-2 review)\n3855\t- `npm run build` called redundantly once in 12-3 dev\n3856\t- `npm run test:unit` called twice in 12-3 verify (verbose then summary)\n3857\t- 12-3 and 13-2 code-review phases had the most tool calls (21 and 25) — these were the stories with the most bugs found\n3858\t\n3859\t### 3.6 Wasted Spend\n3860\t\n3861\t| Source | Estimated Waste | Explanation |\n3862\t|--------|----------------|-------------|\n3863\t| AGENTS.md staleness fixes | ~$3-5 per session | Verify fails, subagent must diagnose and fix before proceeding. Happened 3x this session. |\n3864\t| Proof format rewrites | ~$1-2 per occurrence | Verify subagent generates wrong format, must rewrite. Happened 2x. |\n3865\t| \"unknown\" story bucket | $33.23 (sprint total) | 16.4% of total spend not attributed to any story — orchestrator overhead, retros, misc. |\n3866\t| Duplicate test runs | ~$0.50 per occurrence | test:unit run twice in verify phases |\n3867\t\n3868\t### 3.7 Cost Optimization Opportunities\n3869\t\n3870\t1. **Fix AGENTS.md staleness at dev-story phase, not verify.** Each verify-time fix costs a full context reload. Auto-generating AGENTS.md after dev-story would eliminate ~$3-5/session.\n3871\t2. **Standardize proof format in verify template.** Two format mismatches this session alone. Hardcode the exact expected format in the verify skill prompt.\n3872\t3. **Cache `workflow-engine.test.ts` reads.** This file is read 7+ times across phases. A shared context injection could save repeated reads.\n3873\t4. **Reduce verify phase cost (44% of spend).** Consider: (a) running lint+build as a pre-check before the full verify, (b) failing fast on known blockers, (c) combining some verify steps.\n3874\t5. **Attribute \"unknown\" cost bucket.** $33.23 unattributed — likely orchestrator and retro phases. Better tagging would reveal optimization targets.\n3875\t\n3876\t---\n3877\t\n3878\t## 4. What Went Well\n3879\t\n3880\t- **4 stories completed in ~5 hours** — consistent pace of ~75 min/story through full lifecycle.\n3881\t- **Zero test regressions across all 4 stories.** Suite grew from 4478 to 4506 tests with no breakage.\n3882\t- **Code review caught 3 HIGH bugs:** timer leak, path traversal, empty input validation. All fixed before merge.\n3883\t- **Coverage held steady at 96.8%** — no regression despite 4 new modules.\n3884\t- **Epic 12 (multi-framework drivers) fully completed** — Codex, OpenCode, and health check all shipped.\n3885\t- **Story 13-2 completed despite being unstarted at session begin** — first half of Epic 13 done.\n3886\t- **All 42 ACs passed with evidence** — no escalations, no partial passes.\n3887\t- **Session issues log worked as intended** — every subagent reported issues, enabling this retrospective.\n3888\t\n3889\t---\n3890\t\n3891\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n3892\t\n3893\t- **Verify phase consumes 44% of total sprint cost** — disproportionate to value. Much of this is fighting AGENTS.md staleness and proof format mismatches.\n3894\t- **AGENTS.md staleness is a recurring tax** — blocked verify in 3 of 4 stories. This has been flagged in every session since session 9 and is still not fixed at the process level.\n3895\t- **sprint-state.json epic sync bug persists** — epics 10-15 show `storiesDone: 0` despite stories being done. Flagged multiple sessions ago.\n3896\t- **`codeharness stats --save` broken** — looks for `session-logs/` directory that doesn't exist. Cannot generate cost report from the tool as designed.\n3897\t- **Proof format template drift** — verify subagent produces different formats depending on which model instance runs it. No single source of truth enforced.\n3898\t- **classifyError duplication growing** — now in 3 drivers (claude-code, codex, opencode), ~80 lines each. Deliberately deferred per architecture, but tech debt is accumulating.\n3899\t\n3900\t---\n3901\t\n3902\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n3903\t\n3904\t### Patterns to Repeat\n3905\t- **Code review as mandatory gate** — 3 HIGH bugs caught this session. The ~9% cost is well justified by the security and correctness bugs found.\n3906\t- **Token Report in session issues log** — subagent-level breakdown enables precise cost analysis. Keep requiring this.\n3907\t- **Small, well-scoped stories** — all 4 stories this session were 100-200 lines of production code. Clean, reviewable, verifiable.\n3908\t\n3909\t### Patterns to Avoid\n3910\t- **Deferring AGENTS.md maintenance** — it costs more to fix at verify time than at dev time. Every session pays this tax.\n3911\t- **Guessing proof format** — the verify subagent should have a strict template, not freestyle the format each time.\n3912\t- **Running full test suite twice in verify** — once for verbose output, once for summary. Combine into one run.\n3913\t\n3914\t---\n3915\t\n3916\t## 7. Action Items\n3917\t\n3918\t### Carried Forward (Still Open)\n3919\t\n3920\t| # | Action | Priority | Status |\n3921\t|---|--------|----------|--------|\n3922\t| 41 | Extract shared driver utilities (classifyError, parseLine) into `driver-utils.ts` | MEDIUM | Open — 5 sessions deferred |\n3923\t| 46 | Remove dead fixture files in `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/` | LOW | Open |\n3924\t| 48 | Fix verify proof format template — `## AC N:` not `### AC N:` | MEDIUM | Open |\n3925\t| 50 | Consolidate epic files or add canonical source manifest | MEDIUM | Open |\n3926\t| 53 | Fix sprint-state.json sync — epic storiesDone counters stuck at 0 | HIGH | Open |\n3927\t\n3928\t### New This Session\n3929\t\n3930\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n3931\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n3932\t| 57 | Auto-generate AGENTS.md during dev-story phase (not verify) | HIGH | Process/Tooling |\n3933\t| 58 | Hardcode proof format template in verify skill prompt | MEDIUM | Tooling |\n3934\t| 59 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to find ralph logs path | MEDIUM | Tooling |\n3935\t| 60 | Fix pre-existing `require-yield` lint error in workflow-engine.test.ts:154 | LOW | Cleanup |\n3936\t| 61 | Add `assertSafeComponent` pattern to all file-path-constructing functions | LOW | Cleanup |\n3937\t| 62 | Resolve `output_contract` naming overlap before 13-3 implementation | MEDIUM | Next story |\n3938\t| 63 | Reduce verify phase cost — fail-fast on known blockers, combine test runs | HIGH | Process |\n3939\t\n3940\t### Priority Recommendations for Next Session\n3941\t\n3942\t1. **Story 13-3 (cross-framework-workflow-execution)** — last story in Epic 13. Complete the epic.\n3943\t2. **Fix AGENTS.md auto-generation (action #57)** — highest-impact cost reduction. Saves ~$3-5/session.\n3944\t3. **Fix sprint-state.json epic sync (action #53)** — 3+ sessions of incorrect dashboard data.\n3945\t4. **Extract shared driver utilities (action #41)** — 5 sessions deferred, now 3 drivers with identical code.\n3946\t\n3947\t---\n3948\t\n3949\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 9, Part 3)\n3950\t\n3951\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T14:45:00Z"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01371Pi8Xv61ym8B24cArBdj","session_id":"a29ee53b-c2b0-4802-9455-7215112648b1","uuid":"af2ce7fd-48bc-4b6f-9152-5a422395cf7d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:19:52.668Z"}
