nds, bugs, and observations reported by every subagent that ran this session. These are the raw materials for your retrospective — do not ignore them.\n\nCRITICAL: Run `codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCRITICAL: The session issues log contains `## Token Report` sections from each subagent. Aggregate these to understand WHERE tokens were spent inside subagents (not just the parent). Look for:\n- Which subagent phases had the most tool calls?\n- Which subagents read the same files repeatedly?\n- Which Bash commands produced the largest outputs?\n- What redundant operations were reported?\nInclude this subagent-level breakdown in the cost analysis section.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log:\n   - Bugs discovered during implementation or verification\n   - Workarounds applied (tech debt introduced this session)\n   - Code quality concerns raised by reviewers\n   - Verification gaps (escalated ACs, weak evidence)\n   - Tooling/infrastructure problems (sandbox, permissions, CLI issues)\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report:\n   - Total API-equivalent cost this sprint\n   - Cost per phase (which phases are most expensive?)\n   - Cost per story (which stories cost the most and why?)\n   - Wasted spend (no-op sessions, failed verifications, retries)\n   - Cost optimization opportunities\n4. **What went well** — stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n5. **What went wrong** — failures, blockers, stuck stories, wasted iterations\n6. **Lessons learned** — patterns to repeat or avoid\n7. **Action items** — concrete next steps\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-04-03.md where the date is today.\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"aef250e560ce18eb5","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-04-03.md` (appended with `---` separator after the Session 11 entry).\n\n**Summary of what was produced:**\n\n- **Session 12 retrospective** covering story 14-3 and Epic 14 closure\n- **Cross-session rollup** for Sessions 9-12 (10 stories, 3 epics closed in one day)\n- **Subagent-level cost breakdown**: 734 tool calls tracked across 40 subagent invocations. Read is the most-called tool (34%), `workflow-engine.test.ts` is the most-read file (15+ times)\n- **Wasted spend estimate**: $18-31 (7-12% of $250.40 total), primarily from AGENTS.md staleness fixes and proof format rewrites\n- **Key finding**: Verify phase at 45.5% ($113.94) remains the dominant cost driver. Code review at 8.7% ($21.80) caught 12 HIGH bugs across today's sessions — highest value-per-dollar phase.\n- **Sprint status**: 44/47 stories done (93.6%), 14/15 epics complete, 3 Epic 15 stories remain in backlog\n- **6 new action items** logged, 17 carried forward"}],"totalDurationMs":213403,"totalTokens":53134,"totalToolUseCount":15,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6763,"cache_read_input_tokens":46032,"output_tokens":338,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6763},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
